00:34:50,505 --> 00:34:53,714
[Alvarez] It's one of those things
in post-production,

637
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:57,338
a shame that people
are left without listening

638
00:34:57,429 --> 00:35:00,467
to one of the music queues
that were better

639
00:35:00,557 --> 00:35:02,139
than those that Roque did for this fight.

640
00:35:02,225 --> 00:35:07,265
He made a brutal composition
with flamenco stomping,

641
00:35:07,355 --> 00:35:10,347
with orchestra and everything,
it was amazing.

642
00:35:10,442 --> 00:35:12,058
But then we realized, at some point,

643
00:35:12,152 --> 00:35:15,816
that without music
it was rawer and had more tension,

644
00:35:15,905 --> 00:35:18,988
and in post-production,
we ended up taking it out.

645
00:35:20,577 --> 00:35:22,614
The truth is the fight is very good, raw,

646
00:35:22,704 --> 00:35:25,571
you hear every little noise
of the knife, the hand.

647
00:35:25,665 --> 00:35:28,874
Now, when he grabs his fingers,
you hear the fingers breaking.

648
00:35:29,961 --> 00:35:31,076
[grunts]

