1373
01:15:45,833 --> 01:15:47,915
He was psychologically compromised
for a few days.

1374
01:15:48,002 --> 01:15:50,164
[Sayagues] Yes, compromised and exhausted.

1375
01:15:50,254 --> 01:15:51,540
-[Alvarez] Really?
-[Sayagues] Yes.

1376
01:15:52,465 --> 01:15:57,130
During all that fight, the whole day
of filming was very intense for them.

1377
01:15:58,471 --> 01:16:00,758
[Alvarez]
Those post-production clothes, amazing.

1378
01:16:00,848 --> 01:16:02,009
[Luque] They're so good.

1379
01:16:02,099 --> 01:16:05,342
I think maybe I won't wear anything
for the next movie.

1380
01:16:05,436 --> 01:16:06,801
[Alvarez] All in post-production.

1381
01:16:06,896 --> 01:16:08,057
[Sayagues] So good.

1382
01:16:09,732 --> 01:16:12,599
-The set looks so nice.
-[Alvarez] He's Gary Oldman now.

1383
01:16:12,693 --> 01:16:13,808
[Luque] Yes.

1384
01:16:15,071 --> 01:16:19,440
This one was also brave
because there is no light, supposedly.

1385
01:16:19,533 --> 01:16:23,777
Although, now in the story,
in the internal story clock,

1386
01:16:23,871 --> 01:16:27,205
it's beginning to... to clear up.

1387
01:16:27,291 --> 01:16:30,534
[Alvarez] Yes. It could be street lights.

1388
01:16:30,628 --> 01:16:33,837
But as they say, the light comes
from the same place as music.

1389
01:16:33,923 --> 01:16:37,757
[Luque] Exactly. But, well,
here the idea was a bit

1390
01:16:37,843 --> 01:16:40,926
to establish this same set
in a different way.

1391
01:16:41,722 --> 01:16:44,339
[Alvarez] Raul and the new henchmen
that appeared.

1392
01:16:44,433 --> 01:16:46,390
[Luque] Yes. His friends.

1393
01:16:47,645 --> 01:16:49,135
[Alvarez] Yes. Great shot.

1394
01:16:52,566 --> 01:16:55,058
When did you decide to make it all blue?

1395
01:16:56,320 --> 01:16:57,401
[Sayagues] I'm not sure.

1396
01:16:57,488 --> 01:16:59,820
[Luque] We were talking about it.
I can't remember exactly.

1397
01:16:59,907 --> 01:17:00,942
For me, it was a bit...

1398
01:17:01,033 --> 01:17:05,743
It was natural because
the hole above this basement,

1399
01:17:06,664 --> 01:17:11,079
in the fantasy, it's like an air hole
that's between the buildings.

1400
01:17:12,128 --> 01:17:15,166
[Sayagues] The light got there
from this dawn gloom.

1401
01:17:15,256 --> 01:17:17,748
[Luque] Of dawn. This is awesome, though.

1402
01:17:20,511 --> 01:17:23,879
[Alvarez] It was a way of depicting
how to use even more senses.

1403
01:17:23,973 --> 01:17:27,056
-[Luque] Yes.
-[Alvarez] Now, touch.

1404
01:17:32,273 --> 01:17:35,436
He used smell in the first one.
He'd smell the shoes.

1405
01:17:35,526 --> 01:17:36,516
[Luque] Yes.

1406
01:17:36,610 --> 01:17:39,102
[Alvarez] Obviously,
he uses hearing all the time.

1407
01:17:39,196 --> 01:17:41,688
We have to create a way
for him to use taste.

1408
01:17:41,782 --> 01:17:42,943
[laughter]

1409
01:17:43,033 --> 01:17:44,569
I don't know how.

1410
01:17:47,663 --> 01:17:49,904
[Sayagues] And here,
Raul's arc is completed.

1411
01:17:49,999 --> 01:17:51,831
[Alvarez] Here,
the Blind Man could have died.

1412
01:17:51,917 --> 01:17:54,659
-[Sayagues] He could've killed him, yes.
-[Alvarez] Almost killed.

1413
01:17:56,130 --> 01:18:02,217
But Raylan made a mistake
that was to cross the moral line and...

1414
01:18:02,845 --> 01:18:04,427
that's not cool with Raul.

1415
01:18:04,513 --> 01:18:05,799
[laughter]

1416
01:18:05,890 --> 01:18:07,472
[Raul] You'd better hurry.

1417
01:18:07,558 --> 01:18:09,640
[Luque] Act cool, Raul.

1418
01:18:12,354 --> 01:18:15,096
[Alvarez] That was
a great missed opportunity

1419
01:18:15,191 --> 01:18:17,228
when he says, "That's not cool with me."

1420
01:18:17,318 --> 01:18:19,559
He should've said,
"That's not cool with Raul."

1421
01:18:19,653 --> 01:18:22,236
[laughter]

1422
01:18:22,323 --> 01:18:24,985
-[Luque] Raul here... great.
-[Alvarez] Here, he makes sure that

1423
01:18:25,075 --> 01:18:29,239
he's loosening up now,
because he was also convinced

1424
01:18:29,330 --> 01:18:32,118
that the machete would fly into his head.

1425
01:18:32,208 --> 01:18:33,698
[laughter]

1426
01:18:36,045 --> 01:18:38,457
[Sayagues] Here, we get into
the epic scene of the movie.

1427
01:18:38,547 --> 01:18:42,962
This was the biggest scene.
Actually, it was the most demanding scene.

1428
01:18:43,052 --> 01:18:45,885
[Alvarez] Tito's pool.

1429
01:18:45,971 --> 01:18:47,086
[Sayagues] Marshal Tito's pool.

1430
01:18:47,181 --> 01:18:51,470
Yes, that was the palace,
one of the palaces used by the generals.

1431
01:18:51,560 --> 01:18:54,348
[Alvarez] That location was--
It was one of the houses, right?

1432
01:18:54,438 --> 01:18:58,727
One of the houses in Serbia and...
Belgrade. That was the house of...

1433
01:18:58,817 --> 01:19:00,933
There was more than
one pool in that house, right?

1434
01:19:01,028 --> 01:19:02,564
-[Sayagues] Yes.
-[Luque] It had an outdoor pool.

1435
01:19:02,655 --> 01:19:04,692
But that pool was an indoor one.

1436
01:19:06,033 --> 01:19:10,197
This pool,
it seems that it never worked well.

1437
01:19:10,287 --> 01:19:13,370
[Alvarez] Really?
-[Luque] Apparently, it always had leaks.

1438
01:19:13,457 --> 01:19:15,744
[Alvarez] Look at the depth of that, wow.

1439
01:19:15,834 --> 01:19:18,371
-[Luque] Yes, it's amazing.
-[Alvarez] It's not real.

1440
01:19:18,462 --> 01:19:19,497
[Luque] Right.

1441
01:19:19,588 --> 01:19:21,078
[Alvarez] It was enlarged
in post-production.

1442
01:19:21,173 --> 01:19:23,414
[Sayagues] It's a big scene
with lots of things happening.

1443
01:19:23,509 --> 01:19:25,250
I think it took us
like a whole week to film.

1444
01:19:25,344 --> 01:19:26,505
[Luque] A week and a half.

1445
01:19:26,595 --> 01:19:29,087
-[Sayagues] Yes.
-[Luque] It was very complicated.

1446
01:19:29,181 --> 01:19:30,171
[Alvarez] It's normal.

1447
01:19:30,266 --> 01:19:36,512
The good climaxes of any movie
have to take up 25% of the shooting time.

1448
01:19:36,605 --> 01:19:41,099
[Sayagues] Well, the lighting setup
is also very complex.

1449
01:19:42,611 --> 01:19:44,193
It took days to put that together.

1450
01:19:44,280 --> 01:19:45,987
[Alvarez] Right,
it was a physical location.

1451
01:19:46,073 --> 01:19:47,484
-You had real lights outside.
-[Luque] Yes.

1452
01:19:47,574 --> 01:19:52,489
We had to cover up all of this
with a big tent. It was raining.

1453
01:19:52,579 --> 01:19:55,321
[Alvarez] Right, I was going to ask
what would happen if it rained.

1454
01:19:55,416 --> 01:19:59,455
[Luque] Yes. It was raining hard outside
and we had to put up a big tent.

1455
01:19:59,545 --> 01:20:02,003
The grips there saved the day.

1456
01:20:03,590 --> 01:20:08,881
[Alvarez] I remember we tried
so many different colors for this part.

1457
01:20:09,805 --> 01:20:11,045
[gunshots]

1458
01:20:15,019 --> 01:20:18,557
This was such a great find.

1459
01:20:19,481 --> 01:20:21,438
We made it dark without it being dark.

1460
01:20:21,525 --> 01:20:28,192
It was daytime
and they were all in the same condition.

1461
01:20:29,325 --> 01:20:33,068
With all the smoke,
you couldn't see anything.

1462
01:20:33,871 --> 01:20:36,112
It has a samurai movie vibe.

1463
01:20:37,124 --> 01:20:40,037
Some parts seem as if they were taken
from a Kurosawa movie.

1464
01:20:40,127 --> 01:20:45,463
You have knives,
contrast, and it's all red.

1465
01:20:45,549 --> 01:20:49,668
[Luque] It's exasperating, right?
Not knowing where it can come from.

1466
01:20:49,762 --> 01:20:52,629
[Alvarez] Absolutely.
It feels like one of those movies,

1467
01:20:52,723 --> 01:20:56,557
of a samurai fight in the fog.

1468
01:20:56,643 --> 01:20:57,804
The knives.

1469
01:20:57,895 --> 01:20:59,306
[Luque] Yes, a bladed weapon.

1470
01:20:59,396 --> 01:21:00,386
[Alvarez] Zatoichi.

1471
01:21:06,945 --> 01:21:11,280
This part replicates the first one.

1472
01:21:12,076 --> 01:21:15,910
Where the Blind Man kills Cindy.
He kills a loved one.

1473
01:21:15,996 --> 01:21:22,083
Unintentionally, he kills someone
he was trying to protect.

1474
01:21:22,169 --> 01:21:25,878
[Luque] The consequences of such violence.

1475
01:21:26,590 --> 01:21:28,206
"NO!"

1476
01:21:28,300 --> 01:21:30,712
[grunting]

1477
01:21:32,679 --> 01:21:35,546
Of course, when he screams,
he reveals his position

1478
01:21:35,641 --> 01:21:37,177
and that's when he attacks.

1479
01:21:38,811 --> 01:21:41,269
[Alvarez] But Raylan is furious now.

1480
01:21:41,355 --> 01:21:42,390
<i>Luque) He is.</i>

1481
01:21:42,481 --> 01:21:46,896
[Alvarez] He now has
the strength he needs.

1482
01:21:46,985 --> 01:21:48,475
[Luque] This drives me crazy.

1483
01:21:50,072 --> 01:21:53,190
All this was so hard to shoot.

1484
01:21:53,283 --> 01:21:55,240
-So hard.
-[Alvarez] Yes.

1485
01:21:55,327 --> 01:21:57,944
[Luque] Each shoot has its own thing.

1486
01:22:02,209 --> 01:22:04,371
[gasping]

1487
01:22:05,170 --> 01:22:09,585
[Alvarez] This is metaphorically
the cutting of the umbilical cord.

1488
01:22:09,675 --> 01:22:12,337
[Luque] The bond with her mother.

1489
01:22:12,428 --> 01:22:14,715
[Alvarez] Since the beginning,
you see there's something

1490
01:22:14,805 --> 01:22:16,967
that won't let her move on.

1491
01:22:17,057 --> 01:22:18,343
[Luque] That's right.

1492
01:22:18,434 --> 01:22:19,799
[Alvarez] Her mom. Who she is.

1493
01:22:20,894 --> 01:22:24,057
But her mother
wasn't what we all expected.

1494
01:22:24,148 --> 01:22:25,889
[Luque] She needs to let her go.

1495
01:22:25,983 --> 01:22:27,064
[laughter]

1496
01:22:27,860 --> 01:22:29,646
-Ah.
-[Alvarez] God.

1497
01:22:29,736 --> 01:22:30,726
[screaming]

1498
01:22:32,906 --> 01:22:34,112
Phoenix!

1499
01:22:34,199 --> 01:22:35,655
[Sayagues] She falls anyway.

1500
01:22:35,742 --> 01:22:38,484
[Luque] She falls, but it saves her.

1501
01:22:39,329 --> 01:22:41,536
-Who comes in?
-[Alvarez chuckles]

1502
01:22:42,332 --> 01:22:44,073
[Alvarez] Was that a puppet?

1503
01:22:44,168 --> 01:22:49,834
[Sayagues] There's one.
There's a real dog attacking its trainer

1504
01:22:50,716 --> 01:22:55,802
and here's a puppet, a rubber dog,
that he throws out the window.

1505
01:22:55,888 --> 01:23:01,133
[Luque] There's a broken fake arm,
there's the head biting the arm, too.

1506
01:23:01,226 --> 01:23:04,969
This also demanded
a lot of second unit work.

1507
01:23:07,983 --> 01:23:11,146
[Alvarez] What's funny about
this phrase you'll hear now,

1508
01:23:11,236 --> 01:23:13,898
"Now you're gonna see what I see,”
wasn't in the first movie,

1509
01:23:13,989 --> 01:23:19,029
but was invented
by Sony's marketing department

1510
01:23:19,119 --> 01:23:22,987
for the trailer.

1511
01:23:23,081 --> 01:23:27,040
And the people liked it so much that--

1512
01:23:27,127 --> 01:23:30,370
[Luque] There comes the pudding...

1513
01:23:30,464 --> 01:23:31,795
[laughter]

1514
01:23:31,882 --> 01:23:34,715
This part was complicated, too.

1515
01:23:34,801 --> 01:23:36,633
[Sayagues]
There's digital compositing there--

1516
01:23:36,720 --> 01:23:38,882
[Luque] The tricky thing
was putting the eyes back on.

1517
01:23:38,972 --> 01:23:41,213
Melting them was easy.

1518
01:23:41,308 --> 01:23:43,299
[laughter]

1519
01:23:43,393 --> 01:23:46,101
[Sayagues]
There's digital compositing there.

1520
01:23:46,188 --> 01:23:51,604
There's a silicone head
with that pus inside, and it bleeds.

1521
01:23:51,693 --> 01:23:52,933
[Luque] The eye juice.

1522
01:23:53,028 --> 01:23:54,359
[Sayagues] The eye juice.

1523
01:23:55,489 --> 01:23:58,447
[Luque] Poor Phoenix.
She's alive at least.

1524
01:24:00,202 --> 01:24:01,442
[exclaiming]

1525
01:24:05,040 --> 01:24:06,451
He hears her.

1526
01:24:15,342 --> 01:24:16,423
Stop.

1527
01:24:17,052 --> 01:24:18,634
Stop!

1528
01:24:22,057 --> 01:24:23,172
You...

1529
01:24:25,602 --> 01:24:27,559
You mustn't come near me.

1530
01:24:30,065 --> 01:24:36,061
[Alvarez] The good news is
the Blind Man finally saw.

1531
01:24:36,154 --> 01:24:40,193
At the last moment,
he stopped being morally blind at least.

1532
01:24:40,284 --> 01:24:41,274
[Luque] True.

1533
01:24:41,368 --> 01:24:45,077
[Alvarez] I think he realizes who he is

1534
01:24:45,163 --> 01:24:48,872
when he leaves the house
and finds Hernandez dead,

1535
01:24:48,959 --> 01:24:51,291
that's when he has the revelation.

1536
01:24:51,378 --> 01:24:56,498
The only reason he went there
is to tell Phoenix what he feels.

1537
01:24:56,592 --> 01:25:01,052
To tell her the truth about himself.

1538
01:25:01,138 --> 01:25:03,926
And he's punished for it.

1539
01:25:04,016 --> 01:25:06,974
-[Luque] He pays the maximum price.
-[Alvarez] The ultimate price.

1540
01:25:07,060 --> 01:25:08,221
[Luque] His own life.

1541
01:25:08,312 --> 01:25:13,432
[Alvarez] Not only does he pay
by losing her,

1542
01:25:13,525 --> 01:25:15,516
because she won't stay in his life,

1543
01:25:15,611 --> 01:25:21,527
but he also pays with his life,
for having stayed there.

1544
01:25:21,617 --> 01:25:23,324
[Sayagues] He also went there
to set her free

1545
01:25:23,410 --> 01:25:28,996
so that she won't come back
and try to find him.

1546
01:25:29,082 --> 01:25:32,495
He wants her to know who he really is
and what he has done.

1547
01:25:33,378 --> 01:25:35,790
[Alvarez] He's pushing her away.

1548
01:25:35,881 --> 01:25:40,546
He hopes she can move on with her life.
It's really hard for her.

1549
01:25:42,596 --> 01:25:45,714
Stephen Lang is brilliant in this scene.

1550
01:25:45,807 --> 01:25:47,923
-[Sayagues] He is.
-[Alvarez] He was made for this scene.

1551
01:25:48,018 --> 01:25:49,258
-Go!
-[gasps]

1552
01:25:49,895 --> 01:25:55,106
[Luque] In addition to
all the technicalities it required,

1553
01:25:55,192 --> 01:25:59,481
it had this super special moment.

1554
01:25:59,571 --> 01:26:02,563
[Alvarez] We spent most of the time
shooting the action scenes,

1555
01:26:02,658 --> 01:26:04,148
but not the final monologue.

1556
01:26:04,242 --> 01:26:06,529
[Luque] Just a few days.

1557
01:26:06,620 --> 01:26:08,531
[Alvarez] That's what happened.

1558
01:26:08,622 --> 01:26:10,283
[Luque] We did a good job.

1559
01:26:10,374 --> 01:26:14,459
[Sayagues] We took the time
that was needed.

1560
01:26:14,544 --> 01:26:17,753
He came prepared
and nailed it on the first try.

1561
01:26:17,839 --> 01:26:19,045
[Luque] True.

1562
01:26:22,260 --> 01:26:23,671
[sobbing]

1563
01:26:23,762 --> 01:26:27,050
[Alvarez] If the hand had rested
a bit longer on his shoulder,

1564
01:26:27,140 --> 01:26:30,178
you'd have thought it was Phoenix
telling him, "It's okay."

1565
01:26:30,268 --> 01:26:32,726
-[Sayagues] Yes. But no.
-[Luque] But no.

1566
01:26:34,064 --> 01:26:35,975
[Alvarez]
The Blind Man doesn't fight back.

1567
01:26:36,066 --> 01:26:38,979
-[Sayagues] He's given up.
-[Alvarez] He's ready to die.

1568
01:26:39,069 --> 01:26:40,275
[Sayagues] That's all.

1569
01:26:40,362 --> 01:26:43,150
[Alvarez] He believed
what he had said to her.

1570
01:26:43,240 --> 01:26:46,483
Saying goodbye to her was like dying.

1571
01:26:47,577 --> 01:26:52,788
And by staying there, that's what he got.
He got stabbed in the back.

1572
01:26:52,874 --> 01:26:54,035
[Luque and Sayagues] Yes.

1573
01:26:56,128 --> 01:26:59,746
[Alvarez] That's all for him.

1574
01:27:04,428 --> 01:27:05,759
So Shakespearean.

1575
01:27:05,846 --> 01:27:09,055
[Luque] Totally. And she came back.

1576
01:27:10,809 --> 01:27:11,844
These two are...

1577
01:27:11,935 --> 01:27:14,643
[Alvarez] The loss of his eyes,
it's all a Greek tragedy.

1578
01:27:14,730 --> 01:27:16,266
[laughter]

1579
01:27:17,858 --> 01:27:20,145
But they are together.

1580
01:27:20,235 --> 01:27:21,521
[Luque] Together in death.

1581
01:27:23,697 --> 01:27:25,108
[Alvarez] It's crazy.

1582
01:27:29,911 --> 01:27:33,654
[Luque] And now comes the famous scene.
You can't end without one.

1583
01:27:33,749 --> 01:27:35,865
[Sayagues] You have to do it
at some point.

1584
01:27:36,960 --> 01:27:39,497
[Luque] Leonardo continues
to influence us.

1585
01:27:41,006 --> 01:27:44,920
[Sayagues] This whole moment is
about feeling sorry for the wounded.

1586
01:27:45,010 --> 01:27:47,342
-It's about mercy.
-[Alvarez] Yes.

1587
01:27:47,429 --> 01:27:49,716
One of the best decisions for me,

1588
01:27:49,806 --> 01:27:53,674
completely counterintuitive but incredible

1589
01:27:53,769 --> 01:27:57,387
that made this moment
very rare and special,

1590
01:27:57,481 --> 01:28:00,769
that suited this character perfectly,

1591
01:28:00,859 --> 01:28:05,444
is that in any other movie,
there would be music.

1592
01:28:05,530 --> 01:28:10,900
There would be music in the background
that would make you sad about his death.

1593
01:28:10,994 --> 01:28:13,281
But we consciously decided,

1594
01:28:13,371 --> 01:28:18,286
for all the crimes he committed,
he doesn't deserve any music.

1595
01:28:18,376 --> 01:28:21,243
-[Luque] Nothing.
-[Alvarez] Not even a trumpet.

1596
01:28:21,338 --> 01:28:24,547
[imitating trumpet] Nothing at all.

1597
01:28:24,633 --> 01:28:26,749
So we removed it in post-production.

1598
01:28:26,843 --> 01:28:30,552
And it created
a very demeaning atmosphere.

1599
01:28:30,639 --> 01:28:34,303
We wanted him to die like a dog.

1600
01:28:34,392 --> 01:28:37,976
He didn't deserve any recognition.

1601
01:28:38,063 --> 01:28:41,897
-That's what we tried to express.
-[Luque] Right.

1602
01:28:41,983 --> 01:28:45,977
[Alvarez] That's what we tried to convey.

1603
01:28:46,071 --> 01:28:48,984
But she can't help feeling sorry for him.

1604
01:28:49,074 --> 01:28:54,035
That's what any kid her age would do
in her situation.

1605
01:28:54,120 --> 01:28:56,487
She can't change what she feels,

1606
01:28:56,581 --> 01:28:59,289
which is why this ending
is like a tragedy.

1607
01:28:59,376 --> 01:29:02,459
[Sayagues] She's also heartbroken.
Finding out must be really hard.

1608
01:29:02,546 --> 01:29:06,130
[Alvarez] It's tragic for her,
for the audience,

1609
01:29:06,216 --> 01:29:10,631
who might have expected
a more painful punishment.

1610
01:29:10,720 --> 01:29:13,803
But I think what we did here
is more relatable.

1611
01:29:13,890 --> 01:29:18,054
If he'd received the perfect punishment,

1612
01:29:18,144 --> 01:29:20,476
it wouldn't feel real.
It would be too Hollywood.

1613
01:29:22,941 --> 01:29:24,431
[Sayagues] And here...

1614
01:29:25,944 --> 01:29:30,154
the texture and the light change a bit,
like the world changed.

1615
01:29:30,240 --> 01:29:32,982
-[Alvarez] And this is Detroit again?
-[Luque] This is Detroit again.

1616
01:29:35,537 --> 01:29:39,280
[Sayagues] A new dawn
in the life of Phoenix.

1617
01:29:43,545 --> 01:29:46,003
[Luque] The lighting
was quite expressionistic.

1618
01:29:46,089 --> 01:29:48,501
But it fits perfectly.

1619
01:29:56,057 --> 01:30:00,597
[Alvarez] Now she's accepted, she's free.

1620
01:30:00,687 --> 01:30:03,554
She hasn't accepted her past.

1621
01:30:03,648 --> 01:30:09,064
But she's accepted that she's free
to choose who she wants to be.

1622
01:30:09,154 --> 01:30:11,987
She's now in control of her life.

1623
01:30:12,073 --> 01:30:13,609
-At the end of the story.
-[Sayagues] Yes.

1624
01:30:13,700 --> 01:30:18,991
[Luque] And she accepts the name, Phoenix,
which he gave to her.

1625
01:30:19,080 --> 01:30:24,325
[Alvarez] I don't know if it has to do
with her relationship to her father.

1626
01:30:24,419 --> 01:30:28,128
We don't know yet how she feels
about that relationship.

1627
01:30:28,214 --> 01:30:33,209
Not just yet, but what we do know now
is she's in complete control of her life.

1628
01:30:33,303 --> 01:30:39,766
She has taken control
and she knows everything now.

1629
01:30:39,851 --> 01:30:42,183
She can now have a better life.

1630
01:30:44,022 --> 01:30:51,019
So, this is it. The Spanish commentary
for the movie Don't Breathe 2.

1631
01:30:51,112 --> 01:30:52,523
[Sayagues] That was our movie.

1632
01:30:52,614 --> 01:30:58,030
I hope you have enjoyed
our anecdotes and commentaries.

1633
01:30:59,412 --> 01:31:01,699
[Alvarez] See you soon
for Don't Breathe 3.

1634
01:31:01,790 --> 01:31:03,497
[laughter]

1635
01:31:03,583 --> 01:31:04,698
[Sayagues] See you.

1636
